One should eat not in order to please the palate, but just to keep body
going. When each organ of sense subserves the body and through the body
the soul, its special relish disappears and then alone does it begin to
function in the way nature intended it to do. Any number of experiments is
too small and no sacrifice too great for attaining this symphony with nature.
